HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 381
BY REPRESENTATIVE JACKSON
A RESOLUTION
To express the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death of Julie Boston
Lester and to recognize and honor her life, legacy, and extraordinary contributions
to music education, arts, culture, and community service throughout the state of
Louisiana.
WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the passing of Julie Boston
Lester; and
WHEREAS, Julie W. Boston Lester was born on May 11, 1941, in Lillington, North
Carolina, to Lawton and Nannie Boston and was raised in a family grounded in faith,
education, and service; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Lester attended Fisk University, where she earned a bachelor of arts
degree in music, became a proud member of the Fisk Jubilee Singers, and was initiated into
the Alpha Beta Chapter of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated; she later earned a
master of music education degree from University of Louisiana at Monroe; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Lester devoted nearly four decades of distinguished service to the
students of the Caddo Parish Public Schools as a music educator, mentor, and advocate for
the arts, and she inspired generations of young people through excellence in music education
and cultural enrichment; and
WHEREAS, in 1985, Ms. Lester founded the New Dimensions Youth Chorale and
dedicated herself to preserving and promoting the rich traditions of spirituals, jazz, and
choral music throughout Northwest Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Lester faithfully served her church, community, and numerous civic
and cultural organizations with grace, humility, and unwavering dedication, including
sixty-five years of uninterrupted service as a Golden Life Member of Delta Sigma Theta
Sorority, Incorporated; and
